<i> [upbeat rock music]</i>

15:25.458 --> 15:31.129
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:31.131 --> 15:33.364
<i> - ♪ Things may go
 and things may stay ♪</i>

15:33.366 --> 15:35.366
- We were just walking down
the middle of a road

15:35.368 --> 15:37.669
and a guy waved at us.

15:37.671 --> 15:40.672
<i> "Get out," you know?
 "Get under cover."</i>

15:40.674 --> 15:42.373
<i> [gunshot]</i>

15:42.375 --> 15:44.375
<i> "Get out of the street."</i>

15:44.377 --> 15:46.377
<i> [gunshot]</i>

15:48.682 --> 15:51.449
<i> And that
 was the first sign we had</i>

15:51.451 --> 15:53.117
<i> that things
 were "bad" wrong.</i>

15:53.119 --> 15:55.119
<i> [faint gunshots]</i>

16:00.126 --> 16:04.529
<i> By the time that James and I
 had walked onto campus...</i>

16:04.531 --> 16:07.098
I'm sure over a dozen people
had been murdered...

16:07.100 --> 16:10.501
and we didn't know it.

16:10.503 --> 16:13.004
<i> - This is a KLRN
 news bulletin.</i>

16:13.006 --> 16:15.106
<i> A sniper
 with a high-powered rifle</i>

16:15.108 --> 16:18.142
<i> is firing at persons
 within his range.</i>

16:18.144 --> 16:20.311
<i> All Austin-area residents
 are warned</i>

16:20.313 --> 16:23.314
<i> to stay away from
 the University of Texas area.</i>

16:23.316 --> 16:25.149
- It's an unbelievable sight.

16:25.151 --> 16:27.285
The serene
University of Texas campus,

16:27.287 --> 16:29.654
<i> a temperature approaching
 100 degrees now,</i>

16:29.656 --> 16:32.557
<i> and a madman located on top
 of the University Tower</i>

16:32.559 --> 16:35.626
<i> firing and shooting at any
movable target that he can see.</i>

16:35.628 --> 16:37.996
- The shot that hit me
bypassed me

16:37.998 --> 16:39.697
<i> and ricocheted
 off the building.</i>

16:39.699 --> 16:41.699
<i> Everybody was
 in a state of panic.</i>

16:41.701 --> 16:45.570
<i> - Then what happened?
- Then everybody ran.</i>

16:45.572 --> 16:48.573
- It's like a battle scene.
It's like--There he goes!

16:48.575 --> 16:51.275
And another shot. There are
two different kinds of shots.

16:51.277 --> 16:54.145
<i> Apparently police are
 returning the fire now.</i>

16:57.083 --> 17:00.084
- I got lucky, considering
what happened to other people.

17:00.086 --> 17:02.220
<i> - There's no report
 as to who this man may be,</i>

17:02.222 --> 17:03.721
<i> or what he's doing up there,</i>

17:03.723 --> 17:05.790
<i> or what prompted
 this apparent madness.</i>

17:05.791 --> 17:08.492
- We passed the steps
to the Undergraduate Library.

17:08.494 --> 17:10.461
As we were about
to the corner, he shot.

17:10.463 --> 17:11.662
<i> [gunshots]</i>

17:13.366 --> 17:14.464
<i> And I laid there
 for about...</i>

17:14.467 --> 17:16.534
Oh, probably 15 or 20 minutes.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.368
- We didn't know
who was being killed.

17:20.040 --> 17:22.040
<i> Students on campus
 were being shot.</i>

17:23.542 --> 17:25.710
<i>People were dying.
 [gunshots]</i>

17:25.712 --> 17:27.278
- It was just chaos.

17:30.550 --> 17:32.216
<i> - I was looking
 through the binoculars</i>

17:32.218 --> 17:34.218
when all of a sudden
I realized,

17:34.220 --> 17:36.687
he's pointing that rifle
right at me.

17:36.689 --> 17:40.191
I couldn't believe how close
I'd gotten to being shot.

17:40.193 --> 17:42.527
<i> - We can see the movement
 under the clock</i>

17:42.529 --> 17:44.829
<i> on the south side of
the University of Texas Tower,</i>

17:44.831 --> 17:46.831
<i> and police are returning
 the fire.</i>

17:46.833 --> 17:49.367
- There's this guy
who's shooting

17:49.369 --> 17:50.535
at everyone he can see.

17:50.537 --> 17:52.537
What is the matter with him?

17:52.539 --> 17:54.772
<i> - The man is located
 on the University Tower</i>

17:54.774 --> 17:56.374
<i> observation deck.</i>

17:56.376 --> 17:58.843
<i> Below the clock
 which now shows 12:25</i>

17:58.845 --> 18:01.379
<i> and is shooting.
 He's shooting our direction.</i>

18:01.381 --> 18:03.381
- There was a lot
of suffering,

18:03.383 --> 18:05.516
and we were helpless
to do anything about it.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.185
<i> [sirens wailing]</i>

18:07.187 --> 18:10.188
<i> - I see all of this blood.</i>

18:10.190 --> 18:12.623
<i> And I think...</i>

18:12.625 --> 18:15.293
"I didn't get a chance
to say good-bye

18:15.295 --> 18:19.430
to my mom and dad,
or anything."

18:19.432 --> 18:22.433
<i> [soft piano music]</i>

18:22.435 --> 18:27.738
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:27.740 --> 18:30.641
<i> The ambulance driver
 got a call.</i>

18:30.643 --> 18:33.544
Right around the corner,
there was another person

18:33.546 --> 18:36.747
that they wanted him
to pick up.

18:36.749 --> 18:39.617
<i> Looking out that window,
 it was just a direct shot.</i>

18:40.787 --> 18:42.653
<i> And of course I'm thinking,</i>

18:42.655 --> 18:44.155
<i> "If we don't
 get out of here quick,</i>

18:44.157 --> 18:45.623
"I'm gonna get shot again."

18:47.360 --> 18:49.827
<i> - He knocked a boy
 off a bicycle.</i>

18:49.829 --> 18:51.896
<i> He shot windows
 out of the Texas Union.</i>

18:51.898 --> 18:53.431
<i> [gunshots]</i>

18:53.433 --> 18:54.832
<i> More ambulances
 are screaming</i>

18:54.834 --> 18:56.534
<i> up and down
 the University drag,</i>

18:56.536 --> 18:58.202
<i> and the ambulances
 are apparently carrying</i>

18:58.204 --> 19:00.204
<i> those persons
 who we had reported</i>

19:00.206 --> 19:01.539
<i> as lying on the sidewalk</i>

19:01.541 --> 19:03.774
<i> shot in front
 of the Varsity Theater</i>

19:03.776 --> 19:05.843
<i> and other buildings along
 the University drag.</i>

19:05.845 --> 19:08.246
<i> The University area
 has been cordoned off</i>

19:08.248 --> 19:11.516
<i> and so far we've had reports
 of people being shuttled</i>

19:11.518 --> 19:13.518
<i>to the hospital via ambulances</i>

19:13.520 --> 19:15.586
<i> from practically all
the funeral homes in the city.</i>

19:18.892 --> 19:20.424
<i> - I didn't know at the time,</i>

19:20.426 --> 19:22.760
<i> but I was losing
 a lot of blood.</i>

19:24.464 --> 19:27.532
I felt like I was melting.

19:27.534 --> 19:29.534
[panting]

19:33.373 --> 19:35.540
<i> The heat was just deadly.</i>

19:40.547 --> 19:42.280
<i> The pavement was so hot</i>

19:42.282 --> 19:44.448
<i> that it was burning
 the backs of my legs.</i>

19:46.619 --> 19:49.287
- There was a bunch of students,
and I just hollered out--

19:49.289 --> 19:51.189
"Anybody got a rifle?"

19:51.191 --> 19:52.690
Some old boy said he did.

19:52.692 --> 19:53.824
<i> [gunshot]</i>

20:08.541 --> 20:10.708
- Do you wanna?
- Yeah.

20:10.710 --> 20:13.211
<i> I took the rifle first.</i>

20:13.213 --> 20:15.746
<i> But, see,
 I've never shot a scope.</i>

20:15.748 --> 20:17.381
<i> I was raised a poor boy,</i>

20:17.383 --> 20:19.250
<i> and .22 the biggest thing
 I ever shot.</i>

20:20.520 --> 20:22.520
<i> I was shaking.</i>

20:23.723 --> 20:24.989
<i> And what it was is...</i>

20:24.991 --> 20:27.692
Well, it wasn't
a nervous shake...

20:27.694 --> 20:30.695
It was the wobble.
Yeah, the wobble.

20:30.697 --> 20:31.929
<i> I just couldn't get
 the crosshairs</i>

20:31.931 --> 20:33.798
<i> to center in on nothin'.</i>

20:39.472 --> 20:41.806
<i> That boy said he could
 and... [chuckles]</i>

20:41.808 --> 20:43.674
Lord knows he had
better eyes than I did.

20:48.414 --> 20:50.414
- We were in Parlin Hall
when Billy Speed was shot.

20:50.416 --> 20:52.250
<i> [gunshot]</i>

20:52.252 --> 20:54.452
My God, he hit the cop.

20:54.454 --> 20:55.920
- Billy Speed.
[sighs]

20:58.524 --> 21:00.524
<i> [gunshot]
 I glanced down</i>

21:00.526 --> 21:01.959
<i> and I saw Billy get hit.</i>

21:01.961 --> 21:04.562
Billy!

21:04.564 --> 21:06.731
- We have a man here, just came
from the base of the Tower.

21:06.733 --> 21:09.567
What's your name please, sir?
- Leland Ammons.

21:09.569 --> 21:11.702
- Better duck down
a little bit here.

21:11.704 --> 21:13.871
You were standing beside
the policeman when he was shot?

21:13.873 --> 21:16.407
- Yes.
- Was there just one shot fired?

21:16.409 --> 21:18.509
<i> - Uh, well, he was--
 He opened fire on us</i>

21:18.511 --> 21:20.511
when he saw the,
uh, policeman

21:20.513 --> 21:22.380
with a shotgun converging.

21:22.382 --> 21:24.015
The policeman was walking,
he shot him through

21:24.017 --> 21:27.885
the, uh, support near
the statue of Jefferson Davis.

21:27.887 --> 21:29.887
- The shots came near you
at the time, though?

21:29.889 --> 21:31.722
- Oh, yes.
There were shots all around.

21:31.724 --> 21:33.724
- A couple of students
crept out the back door

21:33.726 --> 21:36.027
and made their way to him.

21:36.029 --> 21:39.030
<i> A girl had taken off her slip</i>

21:39.032 --> 21:41.999
and was using it to try
to stanch the bleeding,

21:42.001 --> 21:43.901
but he was bleeding a lot.

21:43.903 --> 21:46.904
<i> The guy that was with her
 had gotten a little tin cup</i>

21:46.906 --> 21:49.907
<i> and had filled it with water.</i>

21:49.909 --> 21:52.476
It was just like
the cowboy movies, right?

21:52.478 --> 21:54.378
<i> - We, uh,
 did all we could for him.</i>

21:54.380 --> 21:55.980
But whether he was
still conscious when

21:55.982 --> 21:58.549
they carried him off
in the ambulance, we don't know.

21:58.551 --> 21:59.884
Maybe it could be
a superficial wound.

21:59.886 --> 22:01.552
<i> [gunshot]
- Billy!</i>

22:01.554 --> 22:03.721
- I saw him get hit here.

22:03.723 --> 22:06.757
So I-I thought he was gonna
be all right, you know?

22:08.928 --> 22:11.329
<i> - That was the moment
 that separated</i>

22:11.331 --> 22:13.397
<i> the brave people
 from the scared people.</i>

22:14.834 --> 22:16.400
<i> I knew that there was no way</i>

22:16.402 --> 22:18.569
that I was going to go
out there and help him.

22:18.571 --> 22:20.371
I didn't wanna get shot.

22:21.874 --> 22:24.008
<i> That was a defining moment</i>

22:24.010 --> 22:27.111
because I realized
I was a coward.

22:28.981 --> 22:31.982
<i> - I met up with Billy
not a couple hours before that.</i>

22:33.519 --> 22:34.952
<i> We just talked
 a little while.</i>

22:34.954 --> 22:37.588
<i> Just a good ol' boy
 conversation.</i>

22:37.590 --> 22:40.424
<i> - He was gonna quit.
 He said...</i>

22:40.426 --> 22:42.059
<i> He was gonna work
 a couple more months</i>

22:42.061 --> 22:44.061
and then he was gonna quit
and go back to college.

22:44.063 --> 22:45.830
And that's just what
he was gonna do.

22:45.832 --> 22:50.368
And uh, you know, his wife
just had a baby and everything.

22:52.638 --> 22:54.138
<i> [gunshot]</i>

22:55.842 --> 22:58.008
<i>- If I see someone--
 - He asked me. He said...</i>

22:58.010 --> 22:59.543
- Do I shoot him?

22:59.545 --> 23:01.545
- And I said...
[chuckles]

23:01.547 --> 23:03.547
"You shoot
the shit out of him."

23:05.885 --> 23:08.719
<i> [gunshot]</i>

23:08.721 --> 23:11.489
<i> [gunshot]
- Before I got into the Tower,</i>

23:11.491 --> 23:14.492
and this is not too nice,
I took up a position

23:14.494 --> 23:16.827
<i> behind a column
 at the Academic Center.</i>

23:21.667 --> 23:23.667
<i> [gunshot]</i>

23:25.138 --> 23:27.805
<i> And I gave him
 the I-talian digit.</i>

23:31.177 --> 23:32.176
<i> [gunshot]</i>

23:34.514 --> 23:39.417
<i> He fired once at the column
 and hit it.</i>

23:39.419 --> 23:40.751
But he didn't do it again.

23:42.755 --> 23:44.922
<i> I waited until the individual
 started firing</i>

23:44.924 --> 23:46.190
<i> on the east side
 of the Tower--</i>

23:46.192 --> 23:47.191
<i> [gunshot]</i>

23:50.062 --> 23:53.931
<i>And then ran across the street
 into the Tower Building.</i>

23:56.068 --> 23:57.768
<i> [gunshot]</i>

24:03.609 --> 24:05.776
<i> [gunshots]</i>

24:05.778 --> 24:09.547
<i> - You could see the bodies
 lying on the campus.</i>

24:11.551 --> 24:14.151
<i> On the Main Mall.
 [gunshot]</i>

24:14.153 --> 24:17.154
And we knew then
that there was nothing

24:17.156 --> 24:19.156
<i> that could be done
 from that office.</i>

24:19.158 --> 24:22.026
So we were inextricably
drawn closer.

24:32.672 --> 24:35.239
<i> We got up to the statue
 of Jefferson Davis.</i>

24:35.241 --> 24:37.942
<i> People say that that statue
 should be taken down,</i>

24:37.944 --> 24:39.977
<i> that that statue
 has no place being there</i>

24:39.979 --> 24:43.247
because of Jefferson Davis
and all he represents.

24:43.249 --> 24:46.817
<i> But at least on that day,
 it gave me a little shelter.</i>

24:48.654 --> 24:50.654
<i> Across from the Main Mall,
 there was about</i>

24:50.656 --> 24:52.490
<i> a dozen students
 there as well,</i>

24:52.492 --> 24:54.658
<i> all looking
 at the bodies laying there.</i>

24:57.830 --> 25:00.064
<i> And it was frustrating,
 I guess.</i>

25:00.066 --> 25:03.901
<i> Something has to be done,
 but if I go out there?</i>

25:03.903 --> 25:06.704
<i> [gunshot]
I might die.</i>

25:11.711 --> 25:13.744
<i> [camera clicking]</i>

25:16.082 --> 25:18.048
- It was like
a frozen snapshot.

25:18.050 --> 25:21.252
<i> [camera clicks]</i>

25:21.254 --> 25:23.954
<i> Obviously some people
 were still alive</i>

25:23.956 --> 25:27.258
<i> and hiding behind
 small things.</i>

25:27.260 --> 25:30.628
<i> A couple people
 seemed really...dead.</i>

25:31.964 --> 25:33.831
I've never seen a dead body.

25:33.833 --> 25:36.000
<i> I didn't care
 if they bombed the Tower.</i>

25:36.002 --> 25:39.837
I just wanted a plane to come
and take that guy out.

25:39.839 --> 25:42.039
<i>- What else did you see as you
 came through the campus?</i>

25:42.041 --> 25:43.941
Did you see any other
injured persons?

25:43.943 --> 25:46.110
- There's several people laying
out on the Mall at this time.

25:46.112 --> 25:47.945
Three of them may be shot,

25:47.947 --> 25:49.647
<i> and the others may just
 be laying there.</i>

25:49.649 --> 25:51.181
<i> [gunshot]</i>

25:51.183 --> 25:54.251
<i> - A woman was lying
 on her back on the Mall,</i>

25:54.253 --> 25:57.154
and she was
obviously pregnant

25:57.156 --> 26:00.224
<i> and in obvious pain.</i>

26:00.226 --> 26:01.892
It was hard to watch her

26:01.894 --> 26:04.595
<i> and to know that no one
 could get to her</i>

26:04.597 --> 26:06.764
<i> without being shot
 themselves.</i>

26:09.936 --> 26:11.936
<i> - Under the base
 of the Tower,</i>

26:11.938 --> 26:14.104
<i> there were a lot
 of people there.</i>

26:14.106 --> 26:16.941
<i> And they were yelling.</i>

26:16.943 --> 26:18.709
<i> They were saying,</i>

26:18.711 --> 26:21.612
<i> "We've gotta help
 that pregnant woman!"</i>

26:21.614 --> 26:25.115
<i> And then somebody else
 yelled out,</i>

26:25.117 --> 26:28.118
<i>"No, we've gotta help the ones
that there is still hope for."</i>

26:31.791 --> 26:33.123
So I thought...

26:34.627 --> 26:37.127
Well...

26:37.129 --> 26:39.363
I probably wasn't
gonna get help.

26:39.365 --> 26:41.999
- Has any effort been made
to try to get those persons out?

26:42.001 --> 26:43.634
<i> [gunshots]
Another shot. He's still firing</i>

26:43.636 --> 26:45.603
<i> repeatedly from
 the University Tower.</i>

26:48.274 --> 26:50.975
<i> - I was trying to figure out
 what was happening.</i>

26:53.145 --> 26:56.313
I didn't feel pain.

26:56.315 --> 26:58.849
It felt more like
something really heavy

27:03.856 --> 27:06.240
was pressing down on me.

27:06.241 --> 27:08.625
I thought it felt like
an invasion from outer space

27:08.628 --> 27:11.295
<i> because I felt like
 I'd been shot</i>

27:11.297 --> 27:15.299
<i> by some kind
 of antimatter gun.</i>

27:15.301 --> 27:18.002
<i> It felt like that's
 what was happening.</i>

27:19.238 --> 27:22.239
<i> [radio frequencies]</i>

27:25.378 --> 27:28.078
<i> That I was just...dissolving.</i>

27:29.749 --> 27:31.749
<i> [frequencies intensify]</i>

27:35.955 --> 27:37.955
<i> [faint footsteps]</i>

27:45.297 --> 27:50.000
<i> Then at some point
 a girl ran up.</i>

27:50.002 --> 27:52.169
- Please he...
- Are you all right?

27:52.171 --> 27:53.871
<i>Let me help you.
 - She came up</i>

27:53.873 --> 27:56.206
<i> and kind of knelt over me.</i>

27:56.208 --> 28:00.044
<i> And her hair...
 It was red and coming down.</i>

28:00.046 --> 28:03.213
<i> [gunshots]</i>

28:03.215 --> 28:05.883
- Go. Go.

28:05.885 --> 28:08.085
<i> [gunshots]</i>

28:08.087 --> 28:09.319
- Get down.

28:22.735 --> 28:24.735
- What's your name?

28:26.238 --> 28:27.237
- It's Claire.

28:27.239 --> 28:30.074
- Claire?

28:30.076 --> 28:32.076
I'm Rita.

28:34.180 --> 28:36.180
I'm here with you now, okay?

28:40.453 --> 28:42.753
- Her name was Rita.

28:45.257 --> 28:47.091
<i> [gunshot]</i>

28:47.093 --> 28:50.094
<i> - I tried to call
 the store and my wife.</i>

28:50.096 --> 28:52.429
<i> [busy signal]
 [sighs]</i>

28:54.433 --> 28:55.966
<i> The lines were busy.</i>

29:05.311 --> 29:08.011
<i> I saw Officer Day.
 He was alone.</i>

29:08.013 --> 29:10.013
[indistinct chatter]

29:10.015 --> 29:12.015
<i> I went up to him
 and I offered my help to him.</i>

29:12.017 --> 29:13.784
- Let's go this way.
- All right.

29:15.955 --> 29:19.957
<i> - As it went on, I moved
 forward a little bit more.</i>

29:19.959 --> 29:21.425
<i> Kind of inching around,</i>

29:21.427 --> 29:23.160
<i> getting a little bit
 different viewpoint,</i>

29:23.162 --> 29:25.996
<i> that sorta thing,
 as we kept broadcasting.</i>

29:25.998 --> 29:28.465
<i> [gunshots]</i>

29:28.467 --> 29:31.001
<i> I think it's
 kind of a natural instinct.</i>

29:31.003 --> 29:34.171
<i> "Hey, I gotta get closer.
 I gotta see what's going on."</i>

29:34.173 --> 29:37.007
<i>We are not sure that the police
 are returning the fire,</i>

29:37.009 --> 29:39.176
<i> but we do hear the shots
 and we do...</i>

29:39.178 --> 29:41.011
<i> But I wasn't, believe me...
 [gunshot]</i>

29:41.013 --> 29:43.113
I wasn't trying to put myself
in harm's way.

29:43.115 --> 29:44.815
Under the clock
on the south side

29:44.817 --> 29:46.316
of the University
of Texas Tower,

29:46.318 --> 29:48.352
and police
are returning the fire.

29:48.354 --> 29:50.487
<i> [gunshot]
 - I saw this airplane.</i>

29:50.489 --> 29:52.022
<i> circling the tower.</i>

29:52.024 --> 29:54.858
<i> It was a single-engine
 small airplane.</i>

29:54.860 --> 29:57.194
But the drafts
of the heat and the wind,

29:57.196 --> 30:00.531
the airplane just couldn't get
a steady shot of the sniper.

